## Test Data

### Factories / Fixtures

Create reusable test data builders:

```
// Good: factory function with sensible defaults
function createTestUser(overrides = {}) {
  return {
    name: "Test User",
    email: `test-${Date.now()}@example.com`,
    password: "SecurePassword123!",
    role: "member",
    ...overrides,
  };
}

// Usage
const admin = createTestUser({ role: "admin" });
const disabledUser = createTestUser({ isActive: false });
```

**Rules:**
- Never use production data in tests
- Every test creates its own data (no shared mutable state between tests)
- Use unique identifiers (timestamps, UUIDs) to prevent collisions
- Clean up test data after each test (or use transactions that roll back)

