## Mocking Rules

- **Mock external services** (HTTP calls, email, file storage, external service integrations)
- **Mock the database** in unit tests (test business logic, not the DB driver)
- **Use real database** in integration tests (test instance, wiped between runs)
- **Never mock the thing you're testing** (if testing UserService, don't mock UserService)
- **Mock at the boundary** - mock the lowest external dependency, not intermediate layers

```
BANNED: Mocking internal functions to make tests pass
  // This tests nothing meaningful
  jest.mock("./calculateTotal", () => ({ calculateTotal: () => 100 }));
  expect(calculateTotal()).toBe(100);

REQUIRED: Mock external boundary, test real logic
  jest.mock("./database", () => ({ query: jest.fn() }));
  // Now test that YOUR code correctly processes the query result
```

